            <div id="dsq-comment-message-33656" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Bloatware is a revenue stream.  If you&#8217;re asking why your carrier wants more revenue, please consider avoiding this subject entirely until you understand.  You will understand, of course.</p>
<p>My G1 is still working for me, and only because it&#8217;s rooted.  I would feel both left out and abandoned if not.  But we&#8217;re in this space in history where our devices are being obsoleted before they wear out or fail.  The carriers don&#8217;t seem to want to change the subsidy model yet. I wonder what the uptake of Android in Europe is, where most people buy their phones outright.  Hard to keep buying the latest when it&#8217;s only been less than a year.  I&#8217;m thinking a G2 would be nice, but then I see the dual-core Tegra phones coming and I hate buying a new phone now and being left out maybe two months from now.  </p>
<p>But TMO doesn&#8217;t drive all this process.  The makers also drive this, and Samsung may yet lock down their phones too much.  LG is showing the Tegra phone, and I wonder if it can be rooted?  </p>
<p>So far, TMO is the place to be.  And CM is the ROM to run.</p>
