        <div id="dsq-comment-body-33665" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-33665" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>T-Mobile does seem to be one of the most root-friendly carriers out there. At least they didn&#8217;t pull a Verizon and make the phones shut off until factory firmware was installed, or &#8220;Bing&#8221; the Google OS. Hell, they didn&#8217;t even charge for tethering. It&#8217;s included with the G2 as part of an OTA update.</p>
<p>I think magenta listens to its customers in a way, in that instead of making us install custom firmware to get tethering, or installing YABA (yet another bloatware app) to make us pay 30 bucks a month for tethering *cough cough Verizon* they did the right thing and allowed us to have it as part of our native G2 package.</p>
<p>And unlike AT&amp;T/Verizon, they merely throttled us at 5GB, which is easily worked around with a few changes in the system. Much better IMO than making us pay ANOTHER data fee. I would have already paid 60 bucks in internet alone if this had been the case with magenta.</p>
<p>BTW, I&#8217;m running unthrottled at like 6GB usage right now, so huzzah!</p>
</div>
